Rest Assured Class 02

Recap
    1.What is Rest Assured
        - A java library to automate REst API's

    2. What are the principles of Rest Assured?
        - Follows a BDD approach
        -Given- prepare the request
        -When- make the call/ request/ hit endpoint
        -Then- Verification/ Assertions

    3. We may have to manually import some classes
        -import static io.restassured.RestAssured.*;

    4. baseURI it is the same as baseURL (or URI without the endpoint)

    5.Runner collection

    6.What is a runners?
        - A file/class/module where you can set specific specifications for your test cases execution


    -ANALYZE

    We imported all these classes manually

    import static io.restassured.RestAssured.*;
    import static org.hamcrest.Matchers.*;
    import org.junit.FixMethodOrder;
    import org.junit.runners.MethodSorters;